'''Google Cardboard'''是[[Google|Google]]所开发、与[[智能手机|智能手机]]配合使用的[[虚拟现实|虚拟现实]][[头戴式显示器|头戴式显示器]]。该平台以其折叠式纸板头盔命名，旨在以廉价成本，激发对VR应用的兴趣和发展<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.wired.com/2015/05/try-google-cardboard/ | last = Pierce | first = David | title = Google Cardboard is VR's Gateway Drug | date = 2015-05-28 | accessdate = 2015-06-17 | website = Wired | archive-date = 2020-11-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108124634/http://www.wired.com/2015/05/try-google-cardboard/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Cardboard is everything Google Glass never was|url = http://kernelmag.dailydot.com/issue-sections/staff-editorials/13490/google-cardboard-review-plus/|website = kernelmag.dailydot.com|accessdate = 2015-06-28|last = Branstetter|first = Ben|date = 2015-06-28|archive-date = 2015-06-28|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150628161039/http://kernelmag.dailydot.com/issue-sections/staff-editorials/13490/google-cardboard-review-plus/|dead-url = yes}}</ref>。按照Google发布的规范，用户既可以利用廉价简易的元件自行制作头盔，或购买预先做好的头盔。要使用平台，用户须在手机上运行Cardboard兼容的应用，将手机置于头盔后端，透过镜片观看内容<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2016/04/google-vr-clay-bavor/|title=Inside Google’s Plan to Make VR Amazing for Absolutely, Positively Everyone|last=Pierce|first=David|date=2016-04-14|website=Wired Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2016-04-14|archive-date=2017-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170624022856/https://www.wired.com/2016/04/google-vr-clay-bavor|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

该平台由巴黎Google艺术文化学院工程师大卫·科玆（{{lang|en|David Coz}}）和达米恩·亨利（{{lang|en|Damien Henry}}）利用他们20%“创意休息时间”（{{lang|en|Innovation Time Off}}）开发<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnet.com/news/facebook-has-oculus-google-has-cardboard/ |title=Facebook has Oculus, Google has Cardboard |accessdate=2014-08-19 |last=Statt |first=Nick |date=2014-06-25 |newspaper=CNET |archive-date=2020-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130183840/https://www.cnet.com/news/facebook-has-oculus-google-has-cardboard/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，于2014年[[Google_I/O|Google I/O]]开发者大会上亮相，被派发给现场所有观众。Cardboard的[[软件开发工具包|软件开发工具包]]（SDK）向[[Android|Android]]和[[iOS|iOS]]操作系统开发。SDK的VR View允许开发者嵌入网络及他们移动应用中的VR内容。

到2017年3月，Cardboard发货量超过1000万个，1.6亿个Cardboard应用程序上线。乘着Cardboard平台的成功，Google在2016年的Google I/O上宣布了增强VR平台[[Google_Daydream|Daydream]]。

2019年，Cardboard開源。2021年3月，Google停售Cardboard<ref>{{cite news |title=Google Cardboard VR 正式停售 |url=https://cn.engadget.com/google-stops-selling-cardboard-vr-goggles-063019724.html |accessdate=2021-03-04 |archive-date=2021-03-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210310093652/https://cn.engadget.com/google-stops-selling-cardboard-vr-goggles-063019724.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 组装和操作 ==
{{Multiple image|direction=vertical|align=right|image1=Google Cardboard - Fully unfolded, continued.JPG|image2=Assembled Google Cardboard VR mount.jpg|width=200|caption2=组装前（上）和组装后（下）的Cardboard对比图。}}

Google Cardboard头盔利用简单低廉的组件制作。头盔规格由Google设计，零件清单、原理图和组装说明书在其网站上免费提供，让人们从现成的零件中组装Cardboard。预先做好的头盔只能从第三方供应商取得，直到2016年2月，Google开始透过[[Google_Store|Google Store]]销售自家出产的头盔<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.engadget.com/2016/02/29/google-sells-cardboard-through-its-store/|title=Google starts selling Cardboard VR viewers through its store|work=[[Engadget|Engadget]]|publisher=[[AOL|AOL]]|first=Jon|last=Fingas|date=2016-02-29|accessdate=2016-04-03|archive-date=2016-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301042449/http://www.engadget.com/2016/02/29/google-sells-cardboard-through-its-store/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

组装Cardboard头盔的零件有一块切割成精确形状的[[纸板|纸板]]、45mm[[焦距|焦距]][[透镜|透镜]]、[[磁铁|磁铁]]或[[电容式感应|电容式感应]]胶带、[[尼龙搭扣|尼龙搭扣]]（如[[维克罗|维克罗]]）、橡皮圈和可选的[[近场通信|近场通信]]标签。Google为大规模制造提供额外的建议，基于这些计划的预组装套件源于多个供应商，成本不到5美元<ref>{{cite news|title=Google Intensifies Focus on its Cardboard Virtual Reality Device|last=Dougherty|first=Conor|newspaper=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|date=2015-05-28|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/29/technology/google-intensifies-focus-on-its-cardboard-virtual-reality-device.html|accessdate=2015-06-17|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108103104/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/29/technology/google-intensifies-focus-on-its-cardboard-virtual-reality-device.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，这些供应商也制作各种Cardboard。

组件装好后，将智能手机插入设备背部，用所选的紧固装备固定。兼容Google Cardboard的应用程序将智能手机显示的画面分成两个，每个眼睛一个，同时对每个画面进行桶形失真，抵消镜头的[[畸變|枕形失真]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://developers.google.com/cardboard/unity/reference|title=Unity Reference: Google Cardboard|work=developers.google.com|accessdate=2015-06-03|quote=...specifies whether you want the values as seen through the Cardboard lenses (Distorted) or as if no lenses were present (Undistorted). ... When VR Mode is enabled, stereo cameras render side-by-side to this target automatically. Each frame, the result is corrected for distortion and then displayed. ... Implements the same barrel distortion that is performed by the native code.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150617194612/https://developers.google.com/cardboard/unity/reference|archive-date=2015-06-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，形成视野广阔的[[3D眼镜|立体]]（3D）图像。

Cardboard首个版本贴合5.7英寸屏的手机，利用磁铁作为输入按钮，需要用到手机的罗盘传感器。更新版设计于2015年Google I/O发布，磁贴开关换成导电杆，在手机屏幕上触发触摸事件，更好地兼容各种设备。

== 软件 ==
Google提供三套开发Cardboard应用的软件开发工具包，一套用[[Java|Java]]供[[Android|Android]]操作系统使用，一套用[[C♯|C♯]]供[[Unity_(游戏引擎)|Unity]]游戏引擎使用，一套供[[iOS|iOS]]操作系统使用<ref name="goog_Goog">{{Cite web | title = Google Cardboard – Google | work = Google | accessdate = 2015-06-02 | url = https://developers.google.com/cardboard/ | archive-date = 2021-01-27 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210127052720/https://developers.google.com/cardboard | dead-url = no }}</ref>。最初仅支持Android，后来Google在2015年5月的Google I/O会议上宣布iOS支持Unity插件<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.engadget.com/2015/05/28/google-cardboard-is-coming-to-ios/ | work=Engadget | title=Google Cardboard now works on iOS | first=Andrew | last=Tarantola | date=2015-05-28 | accessdate=2015-06-02 | archive-date=2019-04-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190409044944/https://www.engadget.com/2015/05/28/google-cardboard-is-coming-to-ios/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。Cardboard支持的第三方应用在[[Google_Play|Google Play]]商店<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cnet.com/news/five-more-apps-that-work-with-google-cardboard/ | newspaper=CNET | accessdate=2014-08-19 | date=2014-07-17 | last=Broida | first=Rick | title=Five more apps that work with Google Cardboard: Games, flight sims, movie players, and more, all great fits for your Google VR headset. | archive-date=2019-02-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190217061851/https://www.cnet.com/news/five-more-apps-that-work-with-google-cardboard/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>和iOS的上[[App_Store_(iOS)|App Store]]上线。除了原生的Cardboard应用，[[Google_Chrome|Google Chrome]]的VR实验利用[[WebGL|WebGL]]实现，包括[[iPhone|iPhone]]在内的支持WebGL的手机也可以运行Google的网页实验<ref>{{cite web |url=http://vr.chromeexperiments.com/ |title=Virtual Reality |accessdate=2014-08-19 |website=Chrome Experiments |archive-date=2014-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141004153431/http://vr.chromeexperiments.com/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/google-cardboard-works-on-the-iphone-too/ | newspaper=CBS News | accessdate=2014-08-19 | last=Johnson | first=Dave | date=2014-08-18 | title=Google Cardboard works on the iPhone, too | archive-date=2020-12-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202020234/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/google-cardboard-works-on-the-iphone-too/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。在2015年Google I/O上，iOS的Google Cardboard演示应用程序接口发布<ref name=io2015>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Nicole|title=Google Cardboard VR for iPhone hands-on|url=http://www.engadget.com/2015/05/28/google-cardboard-vr-iphone-hands-on/|work=Engadget|date=2015-05-28|accessdate=2015-06-02|archive-date=2019-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190204003455/https://www.engadget.com/2015/05/28/google-cardboard-vr-iphone-hands-on/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2016年1月，Google宣布，软件开发工具包将支持[[3D音频效果|空间音频]]，这种虚拟现实效果能模拟3D空间中出自听众头部外面任何地方的音频<ref name="Eadicicco 2016">{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4180621/google-cardboard-headset-audio/|title=Google's Cheap Virtual Reality Headset Is About to Get Better|website=Time.com|publisher=Time Inc.|last=Eadicicco|first=Lisa|date=2016-01-14|accessdate=2016-01-17|archive-date=2016-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116083304/http://time.com/4180621/google-cardboard-headset-audio/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Google pancakes 2016">{{cite web| author=Martz, Nathan| title=Spatial audio comes to the Cardboard SDK| website=Google Developers Blog| url=http://googledevelopers.blogspot.com/2016/01/spatial-audio-comes-to-cardboard-sdk.html| date=2016-01-13| accessdate=2016-01-17| archive-date=2016-02-27| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160227073155/http://googledevelopers.blogspot.com/2016/01/spatial-audio-comes-to-cardboard-sdk.html| dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2016年3月，Google发布Cardboard SDK扩展应用VR View，允许开发者嵌入网页或移动应用程序中的360度VR内容，适用于桌面、Android和iOS<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/31/11336386/google-vr-view-360-degree-content-embed|title=Google's new VR View tool allows easy embedding of 360-degree content|work=The Verge|publisher=Vox Media|first=James|last=Vincent|date=2016-03-31|accessdate=2016-04-03|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108094727/http://www.theverge.com/2016/3/31/11336386/google-vr-view-360-degree-content-embed|dead-url=no}}</ref>。VR内容发布网页的[[Javascript|Javascript]]和[[HTML|HTML]]代码[[开源软件|开源]]，在[[GitHub|GitHub]]上公布，开发者可自行托管内容<ref>{{cite web|url=https://developers.googleblog.com/2016/03/introducing-vr-view-embed-immersive.html|title=Introducing VR view: embed immersive content into your apps and websites|work=Google Developers Blog|first=Nathan|last=Martz|date=2016-03-30|accessdate=2016-04-03|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125090212/https://developers.googleblog.com/2016/03/introducing-vr-view-embed-immersive.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 衍生品 ==
=== Jump ===
Jump是Google开发的虚拟现实影片制作生态系统，于2015年5月28日在Google I/O大会上公布。如同Google对待Cardboard头盔一样，Google对Jump也开发了由16台摄像机圆状阵列构成的样式，并和公众发布<ref name="verge-jump">{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/28/8681855/google-jump-io-conference-virtual-reality-filmmaking|title=Google Jump is an entire ecosystem for virtual reality film-making|work=The Verge|publisher=Vox Media|first=Sean|last=O'Kane|date=2015-05-28|accessdate=2015-06-09|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108121428/http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/28/8681855/google-jump-io-conference-virtual-reality-filmmaking|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[GoPro|GoPro]]和Google合作，利用自家摄像机搭建阵列<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.androidcentral.com/we-took-look-gopro-google-jump-camera-rig|title=We took a look at the GoPro Google Jump camera array|work=Android Central|publisher=Mobile Nations|first=Justin|last=Duino|date=2015-05-29|accessdate=2015-06-09|archive-date=2020-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200807091926/https://www.androidcentral.com/we-took-look-gopro-google-jump-camera-rig|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但Jump系列理论上支持任何摄像机<ref name="verge-jump"/>。一旦拍好画面，VR视频将由Jump的后端软件“汇编器”编译。汇编器使用计算机摄影和“[[计算机视觉|计算机视觉]]”重建场景，产生数千个中间视点<ref name="verge-jump"/>。通过Jump拍摄的成片可配合Cardboard头盔透过[[YouTube|YouTube]]的立体VR模式观看<ref name="verge-jump"/>。

=== Expeditions ===
Expeditions计划提供透过Google Cardboard头盔的VR课堂体验，让教育人士带着他们的学生进行虚拟的[[实地考察|实地考察]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2015/05/28/google-launches-expeditions-an-app-for-shared-virtual-school-field-trips/#.aw4sk6:9dld|title=Google Launches ‘Expeditions,’ An App For Shared Virtual School Field Trips|work=TechCrunch|publisher=AOL|first=Darrell|last=Etherington|date=2015-05-28|accessdate=2015-06-12|archive-date=2021-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124003440/https://techcrunch.com/2015/05/28/google-launches-expeditions-an-app-for-shared-virtual-school-field-trips/#.aw4sk6:9dld|dead-url=no}}</ref>。该计划也在2015年Google I/O上公布，计划于2015年秋季运行<ref>{{cite web|url=http://venturebeat.com/2015/05/28/google-announces-cardboard-expeditions-to-let-teachers-take-classes-on-field-trips/|title=Google announces Cardboard Expeditions to let teachers take classes on field trips|work=VentureBeat|first=Jordan|last=Novet|date=2015-05-28|accessdate=2015-06-12|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108110349/http://venturebeat.com/2015/05/28/google-announces-cardboard-expeditions-to-let-teachers-take-classes-on-field-trips/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。每个教学套件包内含30个同步的Cardboard头盔和智能手机，以及一个供充当向导的老师使用的平板电脑<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.engadget.com/2015/06/04/google-cardboard-vr-education/|title=Google makes its case for VR by reinventing the field trip|work=Engadget|publisher=AOL|first=Nicole|last=Lee|date=2015-06-04|accessdate=2015-06-12|archive-date=2019-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327090715/https://www.engadget.com/2015/06/04/google-cardboard-vr-education/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有意将计划带到学校的教师可在线注册<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/28/8662873/google-cardboard-virtual-reality-io-2015|title=Google has a new Cardboard headset, and it supports iPhones|work=The Verge|publisher=Vox Media|first=Adi|last=Robertson|date=2015-05-28|accessdate=2015-06-12|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108101922/http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/28/8662873/google-cardboard-virtual-reality-io-2015|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[CNET|CNET]]称Cardboard是“首个面向儿童的虚拟现实平台”<ref>{{cite web | title = Cardboard for kids: Google's bet on the future of VR is children | url = http://www.cnet.com/news/cardboard-for-kids-googles-smart-bet-on-the-future-of-vr-is-on-children/ | accessdate = 2015-06-28 | website = CNET | date = 2015-06-02 | last = Stein | first = Scott | archive-date = 2020-11-08 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108104550/http://www.cnet.com/news/cardboard-for-kids-googles-smart-bet-on-the-future-of-vr-is-on-children/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。到2016年5月，超过100万学生透过该计划进行VR实地考察<ref>{{cite web|url=http://venturebeat.com/2016/05/19/google-is-working-with-imax-and-yi-technology-to-build-jump-ready-vr-camera-rigs/|title=Google is working with IMAX and Yi Technology to build Jump-ready VR camera rigs|work=VentureBeat|first=Jordan|last=Novet|date=2016-05-19|accessdate=2016-07-18|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108125605/http://venturebeat.com/2016/05/19/google-is-working-with-imax-and-yi-technology-to-build-jump-ready-vr-camera-rigs/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 合作与推广 ==
2014年11月，[[沃尔沃集团|沃尔沃]]发布了Volvo牌Cardboard眼睛和Android应用“{{lang|en|Volvo Reality}}”，让用户探索[[富豪XC90|XC90]]<ref>{{cite web|date=2014-11-13|url=http://www.theverge.com/2014/11/13/7217397/volvo-is-using-google-cardboard-to-get-people-inside-its-new-suv|title=Volvo is using Google Cardboard to get people inside its new SUV|last=Ziegler|first=Chris|publisher=Vox Media|work=The Verge|accessdate=2015-06-02|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112040203/http://www.theverge.com/2014/11/13/7217397/volvo-is-using-google-cardboard-to-get-people-inside-its-new-suv|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年2月，玩具制造商[[美泰尔|美泰尔]]联合Google宣布立体头盔{{le|View-Master|View-Master}}的VR版。头盔Android版于2015年秋季发布，iOS和Windows智能手机随后发布<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/columnist/baig/2015/02/13/view-master--of-old-uses-google-cardboard-vr/23297205/ | newspaper=USA Today | accessdate=2015-05-30 | date=2015-02-13 | last=Baig | first=Edward C. | title=View-Master rides Google Cardboard into virtual reality | archive-date=2020-09-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200906033627/https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/columnist/baig/2015/02/13/view-master--of-old-uses-google-cardboard-vr/23297205/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

Google也和[[LG电子|LG电子]]合作，为[[LG_G3|LG G3]]定制Cardboard头盔“VR for G3”。该免费配件于2015年2月发布，在某些国家或地区连同新的G3机型派发，被视为[[三星Gear_VR|三星Gear VR]]配件的有力竞争者<ref name="cnet-vrforg3">{{cite web|title=For LG's G3, virtual reality is just a bundle away|url=http://www.cnet.com/news/lg-to-give-away-new-vr-for-g3-headsets/|website=CNET|accessdate=2015-09-25|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129100658/https://www.cnet.com/news/lg-to-give-away-new-vr-for-g3-headsets/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2015年11月8日，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》面向所有家庭订阅户派发Google Cardboard。读者用智能手机下载“NYT VR”应用程序，可享受沉浸式VR环境的新闻阅读体验<ref>{{cite news | url = http://mobile.nytimes.com/2015/11/08/magazine/nyt-vr-how-to-experience-a-new-form-of-storytelling-from-the-times.html | title = NYT VR: How to Experience a New Form of Storytelling From The Times | date = 2015-11-05 | newspaper = New York Times | accessdate = 2015-11-07 | archive-date = 2017-07-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170729141509/https://mobile.nytimes.com/2015/11/08/magazine/nyt-vr-how-to-experience-a-new-form-of-storytelling-from-the-times.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

